               <msContents>
                  <summary>The manuscript contains the following texts (cp. EMML 1495):
 I)
                     ʾAmmǝstu ʾaʿmāda mǝśṭir “The Five Pillars of Mystery" (fols. 1r-11r;
                     69r-126v)
 I-1) Introduction (fols. 1r-3r)
 I-2) Mǝśṭira Śǝllāse
                     “Mystery of the Trinity” (fols. 3v-11r), including Mǝśṭira täwahǝdo “Mystery of
                     the Unity” (fols. 6v-11r)
 II) Maṣḥafa śǝnä fǝṭrat "Book of the Beauty of
                     Creation" (fols. 11r-69r)
 II-1) Sunday (fols. 11r-31r)
 II-2) Monday
                     (fol. 31r-33r)
 II-3) Tuesday (fols. 33r-37v)
 II-4) Wednesday (fols.
                     37v-45r)
 II-5) Thursday (fols. 45r-47v)
 II-6) Friday (fols.
                     47v-57v)
 II-7) Saturday (fols. 57v-63v)
 II-8) Creation of Eve (fols.
                     64r-69r)
 I-3) Mǝśṭira śǝggāwe “Mystery of the Incarnation” (69r-104r)
                     I-4) Mǝśṭira ṭǝmqat “Mystery of Baptism” (fols. 104r-111r)
 I-5) Mǝśṭira
                     qʷǝrbān “Mystery of the Eucharist” (fols. 111r-119r)
 I-6) Mǝśṭira tǝnśāʾe
                     mutān “Mystery of the Resurrection of the Dead” (fols. 119r-124v)
 I-7)
                     Conclusion: authenticity of this teaching (fols. 124v-125r)
 I-8) Treatise
                     on the birth of Jesus (fols. 125v-126v)
 III) Nagara hāymānot “Discourse on
                     Faith” (fols. 127r-128v), incomplete
 IV) Christian interpretation of
                     Moses’ life (?) (129r-132v), unidentified
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
