                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text IV (unidentified) is preceded by two notes on <locus target="#128v">128v</locus>:</note>
                     <note>1) Note on symbolic interpretation of the covenant made between Abraham
                        and Abimelech:</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>ወነሥአ: አብርሃም: አልህምተ: ወወሀቦሙ: ወአቀመ: ፸ አባግዓ: ባሕቲቶን: … “Abraham took cows and
                        gave them (to Abimelech). And he set seventy lambs by themselves …” (s. Gen.
                        21:27-31)</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>2) Note on the purity and perpetual virginity of Mary:</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>አእሚሮ: ከሀሌ: ኵሉ: ከመ: ይለብስ: ሥጋ: እጓለ: እመሕያው: ፈጠራ: ለቅድስት: ድንግል: ውስተ: ከርሠ: እማ:
                        … “Knowing that He assumes the body of mankind, the Omnipotent created the
                        Holy Virgin in the womb of her mother …”</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
