                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; two initial lines on the incipit page
                           of Texts I, II, III, IV; two initial lines of some sections of Text I;
                           two pairs of initial lines of section I-3 alternating with black lines;
                           two initial lines of section I-2; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals; quire marks.
 Some terms and words,
                           like ḥatäta (e.g. fols. 1rv, 3rv, 4rv), täśäṭwo (e.g. fols. 1-4),
                           ʾǝm-maṣḥaf (fol. 13v), tǝrgʷāme (fol. 13v), zǝntu wǝʾǝtu (fol. 21r),
                           kǝfǝl qadāmāwi (fol. 11r), täfṣametä mǝnbab (fol. 31r).</seg>
                     </handNote>
